A favicon is a small image displayed next to the page title in the browser tab
How to add a favicon in HTML
You can use any image as your favicon
A favicon is a small image, so it should be simple image with high contrast

Soooo ooooo lil image in tab, is called favicon

To add a favicon to my website, either save the favicon image to the root directory of your
webserver, or create a folder in the rooot directory called images, and save your favicon image in
this folder. A common name for a favicon image is “favicon.ico”
Next add a <link> element to your “index.html” file after the <title> element; like this

Chapter summary

Use the HTML <link> element to insert a favicon
<link> defines the relationship between a document and an external resource
